n'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The HCPC, like the GSCC it replaced, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">frustrates</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proper complaints against social workers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by ignoring, misdirecting, and mischaracterizing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">those </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">complaints</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The HCPC is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">unaccountable. It is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">one part of a system that protects </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">health </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">workers and frustrates complaints. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In practice, s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ocial workers are unaccountable, the HCPC is unaccountable, the Ombudsman is unaccountable, the Department of Health is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> unaccountable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to complainants</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Each of these authorities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">frustrated my complaints over </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">five </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">years by denying responsibilities, refusing my complaints, mischaracterising my complaints, and investigating my complaints selectively.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">BACKGROUND: </span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In 2008, a s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ocial worker</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (Lynda Deacon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, E/1071687</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> falsely accused me of abusing my ex wife and her son</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. She</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was paid by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">my </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ex wife</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. She relied entirely on hearsay. She</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> never</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> questioned this hearsay,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> contacted me</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> or verified </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> hearsay</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">At that time the GSCC was responsible for social workers. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">When I complained about her to GSCC, she threatened me by email with litigation and warned me that she sat on the GSCC.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The GSCC refused to investigate. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The GSCC falsely claimed that I had submitted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> court documents that it could not consider, but I had not. Then the GSCC falsely claimed that the social worker had violate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> no codes, but I had specified the codes that the social worker had violated. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I then complained to the Ombudsman, but the GSCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sely </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">claimed that I had not completed its complaint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> procedure. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I went back to the Ombudsman three times; each time the GSCC falsely claimed to the Ombudsman that I had not completed some part of the complaint. In fact, the initial complaint was entirely p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">roper, as the GSCC eventually admitted.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The GSCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> eventually investigated the social worker but found she was not acting as a social worker and had done nothing reflecting on her status as a social worker. The GSCC interviewed her several times without givi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ng me any right of reply.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The GSCC accepted her testimony without question, even though my own statement and evidence contradicted her.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> I learnt later that the GSCC promoted her sometime during that same period.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The social worker lied in her testimony: sh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e falsely claimed to have contacted me, falsely claimed to have been ordered by the court to write a report, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">falsely</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> claimed that she did not intend for it to be entered into family court</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, even though </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">she had signed the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">declaration to the family court </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> I had already provided her declaration as evidence</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in my complaint to the GSCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">!</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">THE HCPC REFUSE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> TO INVESTIGATE LEGITIMATE COMPLAINTS: </span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In 2012, t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he GSCC delayed it</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> final response to the very month when it was being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dissolved</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">its responsibilities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">were </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">absorbed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HPC, which became the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HCPC. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I complained to the HCPC about the social worker’s false testimony, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the HCPC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">first </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">falsely </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">claimed that it had</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> no responsibility for social workers, then that the GSCC had already investigated, then opened an investigation, then clos</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed it claiming no new evidence, even though I had submitted the new evidence being the social worker’s contradictory and provably fal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">se testimony. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the process, the HCPC engaged in the familiar practice of ignoring and mischaracterising my submissions. Here are the events of my final complaint to the HCPC:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5 July 2012: I submitted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">properl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y completed complaint form</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by email to the HPC’s email address (</span><a href="mailto:ftp@hpc-uk.org"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">ftp@hpc-uk.org</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) for Fitness to Practice cases. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The HPC, thence the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HCPC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> never acknowledged my submission.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I have copied below the complaint, unedited, from the complaint form.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Deacon is a registered social worker and nurse who took money from my ex-wife to write a defamatory document (dated 24 February 2008) that accused me of the disgusting crimes of “both spousal and child abuse” and recommended that I should be criminally pro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">secuted, based on nothing but malicious hearsay and biases, without contacting me or any other witnesses or admitting my ex-wife’s motivations or incredibility. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Deacon’s document is not a court document</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">– it is not even marked as confidential. It </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">specifies no intended recipients or destination. She does not address the report to anybody or specify who asked for the report: “I have been asked to write a report on my work with the above child.” She was asked by my ex-wife alone, who paid for it. She </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">attempted (23 March 2008) to admit this report into family court during a dispute about property, but the court ruled it as inadmissible, yet it was used to defame me outside of court. No child was at issue in court. No court ever has requested or admitted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> this report. Deacon and my ex-wife contacted no criminal authorities. They used this report to slander me and for material gain during a dispute about property.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Deacon’s document is defamation by a self-identified carer exploiting her qualifications as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">carer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. Deacon’s report began with a list of all her credentials, followed by a description: “I am a qualified psychiatric nurse, a qualified Deacon and a qualified practice teacher in social work.” (This document is attached.)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">I struggled for two years </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">in family court with my ex-wife raising new false issues like this (the judgment condemned her for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">tortious</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> interference, breaches of trust, and incredible evidence). After completing family court, I complained about Deacon (Deacon was never an issue in fa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">mily court), but Deacon interfered with my complaints. </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">On 10 February 2010, after Deacon had learnt that I had complained to her employer, Deacon emailed me, without my solicitation, through my </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Facebook</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> page (this email is attached). Deacon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> queried, reint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">erpreted, prejudiced, and threatened my complaint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. Deacon’s email threatened me with a lawsuit for libel and that the US government would rescind my residency. Her email is overwhelmingly prejudicial and threatening. Deacon’s email spent much of its text q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">uestioning me on my case, defending herself, and threatening me. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The email invited me to complain to the GSCC but warned me that she sat on the GSCC. I took this is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">a warning of bias that should discourage my complaint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. I had complained to the GSCC alread</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">y and understood from the tone of Deacon’s email </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">that she was responding to my prior complaint to the GSCC, not encouraging me to start a complaint. In her email</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> she stated that she was aware of my complaint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> and that the GSCC was the proper authority. Subs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">equently, in October 2011, Deacon told the GSCC that she had emailed me before receiving the notification from the GSCC about my complaint, even though</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> her email is dated later than my complaint and the GSCC’s notification to her of my complaint</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">In her </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">communications, Deacon contradicted herself and lied about her actions:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">In her email of 10 February 2010, she wrote. “I did not write it for the court and had been assured by Ms. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Ansley</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> that she had not submitted it… I am still mystified as to how this got</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> into the court arena as I was assured by Ms. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Ansley</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> that this was not the case”. But in her statement to the GSCC (as reported in the GSCC’s letter to me of 9 December 2011) she claimed that "a court in California" had requested her report - although she </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">lost the request from the mystery "court".</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">In her email to me she claimed that she “had been assured by Ms. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Ansley</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> that she had not submitted it…I am still mystified as to how this got into the court arena as I was assured by Ms. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Ansley</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> that this was not t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">he case”. But Deacon signed the declaration to the court, by hand, as Lynda Ann Deacon (on 18 March 2008). In short, Deacon was NOT requested by the court to submit the report, but DID knowingly submit the report to the court. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Deacon lied about both of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">se facts. </span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">In her email to me Deacon claimed that Deacon’s report was a therapeutic report and not an investigation and thus did not need to investigate my side of the story. This claim is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">factually incorrect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. Deacon’s “report” describes her travel to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">US in order to take a statement and make accusations on the orders and at the expense of my ex wife. It describes no therapeutic activities.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:4.5pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:itali