'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">authorities</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> reconstituted with clear obligations to investigate complaints</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">At the moment, British regulation of healthcare is spineless – full of redundancies, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">deniability, obstructionism, incestuous collusion, and self-regulation, encouraged by a government that does not want to be implicated by oversight.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Do not allow the new authorities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> to hire from the professions they’re supposed to be investigating</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. If empl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">oyees of the HCPC and Ombudsman want to be hired by the new authorities, the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ir past propriety should be investigated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> or the public should be invited to comment. Otherwise, people like Lynda Deacon can continue to serve on her profession’s council without t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he public knowing her clear unsuitability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. If you want to change that culture, you </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">must</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> change the peopl